  "prompt": "Which is a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Coffee County AL?",
  "response": "I don't have real-time access to databases or the internet to provide current recommendations, but I can suggest a few steps to help you find a good inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Coffee County, Alabama:\n\n1. **Search Online Directories**: Websites like SAMHSA (Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration) provide a searchable database of treatment facilities. You can look for accredited rehab centers in your area.\n\n2. **Local Health Departments**: Contact the Coffee County health department or local hospitals for referrals to rehab centers that they work with.\n\n3. **Community Resources**: Reach out to local community centers or support groups. Organizations like Alcoholics Anonymous (AA) or Narcotics Anonymous (NA) can often provide helpful information and lead you to local facilities.\n\n4. **Consult with Healthcare Providers**: If you or a loved one has a primary healthcare provider, they might have recommendations for reputable rehab facilities.\n\n5. **Reviews and Accreditation**: Look for centers that are accredited by organizations such as the Joint Commission or CARF and have positive reviews from former patients.\n\nIf you need immediate assistance, consider contacting a national helpline for support in finding a treatment facility.",
